  <text>
    <body><div type="letter">
      <p>Tuesday 4 o'clock</p>
      <p>Dearest W. I have just had a long &amp; interesting visit from Greig, of which the only misfortune is that it leaves me no time for you this afternoon.</p>
      <p>We are all well &amp; happy, &amp; I getting out of my stupid state. I suppose that nothing will come; &amp; am glad of it;</p>
      <p>for the continued irregularity certainly favors the possible presumption that everything may be about ceasing; altho' this change might probably occupy many months or years to be entirely effected.</p>
      <p>But it is one, as you know, that I should rejoice in.--</p>
      <p>Ralph is getting a little better decidedly now. This is a comfort.</p>
    </div></body>
